The Interpublic Group of Companies, Inc. (IPG) is a publicly traded advertising company.
The company consists of three major networks: McCann Worldgroup, Lowe and Partners, and FCB. Its media agencies are bundled under the IPG Mediabrands entity. It also owns a number of specialty agencies, including public relations, sports marketing, talent representation, and healthcare.[4]It is now one of the "Big Four" agency companies, alongside WPP, Publicis and Omnicom.[5] Michael Roth is the current CEO.[1]



